law.text:
A security interest arising under KRS 355.2-401, 355.2-505, 355.2-711(3), or 355.2A-508(5) is subject to this article. However, until the debtor obtains possession of the goods:
The security interest is enforceable, even if KRS 355.9-203(2)(c) has not been satisfied;
Filing is not required to perfect the security interest;
The rights of the secured party after default by the debtor are governed by Article 2 or 2A of this chapter; and
The security interest has priority over a conflicting security interest created by the debtor.
